# Push Code Workflow

When the user says **"Push Code"** or **"push code"** or **"push to repo"**, follow this workflow:

## Step 1: Check for Changes
Run `git status` to see what files have been modified, added, or deleted.

```bash
cd /Users/sunny/Desktop/Sunny/Projects/Personal_Github/Websites/Nuvaro && git status
```

## Step 2: Minify CSS (if style.css changed)
If `styles/style.css` was modified, minify it:

```bash
cat styles/style.css | tr -d '\n' | sed 's/  */ /g' | sed 's/ *{ */{/g' | sed 's/ *} */}/g' | sed 's/ *: */:/g' | sed 's/ *; */;/g' | sed 's/;}/}/g' > styles/style.min.css
```

## Step 3: Ask for Commit Message
Use AskQuestion tool to get the commit message from the user:

```
"What commit message would you like to use?"
```

## Step 4: Stage, Commit, and Push
Run the git commands:

```bash
cd /Users/sunny/Desktop/Sunny/Projects/Personal_Github/Websites/Nuvaro && git add . && git commit -m "COMMIT_MESSAGE" && git push origin main
```

